1
00:00:01,022 --> 00:00:03,147
<i>Previously on "Prison Break":</i>

2
00:00:03,230 --> 00:00:06,690
We're through the hard part.
Another 18 inches, we'll hit that pipe.

3
00:00:06,773 --> 00:00:07,982
We'll be there by Friday.

4
00:00:12,441 --> 00:00:16,567
Now, we got a hell of a lot
to talk about, don't we?

5
00:00:17,775 --> 00:00:22,651
- This guy says he's on the job in here.
- Concrete is my speciality.

6
00:00:22,735 --> 00:00:24,694
OK, boss. Sign him up.

7
00:00:24,777 --> 00:00:29,820
Whites don't want you, blacks don't want you.
You're just caught in the middle, aren't you?

8
00:00:29,904 --> 00:00:31,696
A regular tweener.

9
00:00:31,779 --> 00:00:34,363
- Hello?
- It's me. It's time.

10
00:00:34,446 --> 00:00:35,280
Yes.

11
00:00:35,363 --> 00:00:37,071
Why are you so cynical?

12
00:00:37,155 --> 00:00:39,697
I think there's cynicism
and then there's realism.

13
00:00:39,780 --> 00:00:42,240
And there's optimism. Hope. Faith.

14
00:00:42,323 --> 00:00:44,657
Thank you for trying to make me smile.
Not today.

15
00:00:45,407 --> 00:00:47,491
<i>You never know.</i>

16
00:00:48,450 --> 00:00:52,159
You want the Cooper story?
I can't give it to you.

17
00:00:52,242 --> 00:00:53,492
Cos I'm not him.

18
00:00:53,576 --> 00:00:56,243
The lawyers, they're still running around.

19
00:00:56,327 --> 00:00:59,994
Same thing goes for the kid.
You gotta hand the reins over to me. Now.

20
00:01:00,077 --> 00:01:01,578
First of all...

21
00:01:01,661 --> 00:01:04,745
You and your partner
are off the job until further notice.

22
00:01:50,174 --> 00:01:53,133
<i>- That one.
- Nice choice.</i>

23
00:01:53,216 --> 00:01:55,883
Platinum. Brushed.

24
00:01:55,966 --> 00:01:58,717
- 6.25?
- 6.25.

25
00:01:59,676 --> 00:02:02,135
She's a lucky woman.

26
00:02:02,219 --> 00:02:03,885
Yes.

27
00:02:04,385 --> 00:02:06,260
She is.

28
00:02:11,221 --> 00:02:14,262
- You kept it.
- Kept what?

29
00:02:14,346 --> 00:02:19,139
- The flower.
- I'm a pack rat. I never throw anything out.

30
00:02:19,223 --> 00:02:22,723
Yeah. All this clutter, it's overwhelming.

31
00:02:23,182 --> 00:02:25,891
- You should see my apartment.
- Whoa.

32
00:02:25,973 --> 00:02:30,350
Haven't even had our first date yet,
and you're already inviting me in.

33
00:02:30,433 --> 00:02:36,392
- I thought you were a nice girl.
- Michael, we all know nice girls finish last.

34
00:02:36,476 --> 00:02:38,644
So where do you finish?

35
00:02:38,727 --> 00:02:41,603
That depends on where I start.
Deep breath.

36
00:02:43,353 --> 00:02:45,437
Exhale.

37
00:02:46,895 --> 00:02:48,812
Inhale.

38
00:02:56,689 --> 00:02:58,898
Sara, we're backing up out here.

39
00:02:58,981 --> 00:03:01,732
Right. I'm sorry.

40
00:03:04,024 --> 00:03:06,317
I'm gonna get your shot.

41
00:03:42,825 --> 00:03:45,326
This is not what I signed on for.

44
00:03:51,244 --> 00:03:56,079
Vice President Reynolds funnelled millions
of dollars into her brother's company.

45
00:03:56,162 --> 00:04:01,205
That money was filtered into small accounts
that made small donations to her campaign,

46
00:04:01,288 --> 00:04:03,830
setting her up to be
the leader of the Free World.

47
00:04:03,914 --> 00:04:06,623
This doesn't end
with us stopping an execution.

48
00:04:06,706 --> 00:04:09,290
<i>For me it does.</i>

49
00:04:29,252 --> 00:04:33,128
OK. Let's rotate.

50
00:04:33,212 --> 00:04:35,879
Sergeant Sodomy, you're up next.

51
00:04:36,921 --> 00:04:38,380
Yo.

52
00:04:40,089 --> 00:04:43,547
- Come on.
- I don't know about y'all, but...

53
00:04:44,590 --> 00:04:48,924
This room is getting
a little too dark for me to dig.

54
00:04:49,007 --> 00:04:54,926
Are you telling me that there's a hole
in Fox River that you don't want to get into?

55
00:04:56,676 --> 00:04:58,593
Hey. No one gets hurt.

56
00:04:59,468 --> 00:05:02,052
Hey, you know, I got a question.

57
00:05:02,135 --> 00:05:05,261
Now, how come Fusilli over here
ain't grabbing a shovel?

58
00:05:05,345 --> 00:05:07,428
I handle arrangements on the outside.

59
00:05:07,512 --> 00:05:10,012
Really? What is that?
Transport, paper, what?

60
00:05:10,096 --> 00:05:12,222
Exactly. Makes me manager.

61
00:05:12,304 --> 00:05:17,390
- And that makes us just labour, right?
- Mm-hm. Now you're getting it.

62
00:05:18,473 --> 00:05:22,807
You know, management better keep
a close eye on the conditions up in here.

63
00:05:22,890 --> 00:05:24,974
Or the labour's liable to go on strike.

64
00:05:25,058 --> 00:05:28,975
- Get back to work.
- Whoa, CO coming.

65
00:05:30,309 --> 00:05:32,476
<i>Hurry, you guys.</i>

66
00:05:34,851 --> 00:05:36,936
Come on, cover it up.

67
00:05:40,812 --> 00:05:43,104
Put that back up there.

68
00:05:46,021 --> 00:05:48,188
Scofield. Move it.

69
00:05:48,271 --> 00:05:50,522
It's time for your conjugal.

70
00:05:52,231 --> 00:05:54,606
Your wife is here.

71
00:05:56,921 --> 00:06:02,021


72
00:06:35,401 --> 00:06:38,277
So you're Mrs Scofield?

73
00:06:38,360 --> 00:06:40,944
Ever done this before?

74
00:06:41,027 --> 00:06:43,278
Had a conjugal, I mean.

75
00:06:43,361 --> 00:06:44,444
<i>No.</i>

76
00:06:44,528 --> 00:06:48,988
Don't worry,
I'm just trying to make conversation.

77
00:06:50,696 --> 00:06:52,780
Clear.

78
00:06:57,072 --> 00:06:59,240
She look familiar to you?

79
00:06:59,323 --> 00:07:01,407
No, Captain.

80
00:07:03,615 --> 00:07:06,491
I know her from somewhere.

81
00:07:11,742 --> 00:07:13,493
You came.

82
00:07:13,576 --> 00:07:15,743
Of course.

83
00:07:15,827 --> 00:07:20,661
- How've you been?
- Fine. I found ajob.

84
00:07:20,744 --> 00:07:23,037
Good. I'm glad.

85
00:07:24,829 --> 00:07:27,579
Is it awful, being here?

86
00:07:27,663 --> 00:07:32,706
Remember the first place you stayed?
That hotel, by the airport?

87
00:07:32,789 --> 00:07:36,206
Only difference is $69 and the free shampoo.

88
00:07:37,249 --> 00:07:39,332
Always the brave face.

89
00:07:40,999 --> 00:07:43,250
You're still wearing it.

90
00:07:43,333 --> 00:07:45,834
Every day.

91
00:07:45,917 --> 00:07:47,876
I worry about you.

92
00:07:47,959 --> 00:07:49,710
Don't.

93
00:07:49,793 --> 00:07:53,044
Is there anything else that I can do?

94
00:07:53,128 --> 00:07:56,211
Just what we agreed on.

95
00:07:56,294 --> 00:08:00,295
I was so nervous when they were checking.

96
00:08:00,379 --> 00:08:02,963
One question.

97
00:08:03,046 --> 00:08:06,505
Why would you need a credit card in prison?

98
00:08:07,548 --> 00:08:10,923
The riot didn't change anything.
Have you seen the budget cuts?

99
00:08:11,006 --> 00:08:14,382
- Another 10% from healthcare.
- And 35 from prevention.

100
00:08:14,465 --> 00:08:16,633
He's the governor, but also your father.

101
00:08:16,717 --> 00:08:21,551
Maybe he thinks if he cuts enough,
they can't afford you.

102
00:08:24,009 --> 00:08:25,802
<i>Thank you.</i>

103
00:08:32,845 --> 00:08:37,138
You understand this is standard procedure
following a conjugal, right?

104
00:08:37,221 --> 00:08:39,304
Never can be too careful.

105
00:08:39,388 --> 00:08:41,680
All right. Bend over.

106
00:08:43,305 --> 00:08:47,140
You have a good time
in the romper room with that Euro?

107
00:08:47,223 --> 00:08:49,807
Whatever you say, boss.

108
00:08:49,890 --> 00:08:52,307
- She come around here before?
- First time.

109
00:08:52,391 --> 00:08:57,684
You sure? Cos damn
if I don't recognise her from somewhere.

110
00:08:57,767 --> 00:09:02,144
Maybe she visits some other con.
Killing two birds with one bone.

111
00:09:02,227 --> 00:09:05,727
- Catching my drift?
- I wouldn't know.

112
00:09:05,811 --> 00:09:08,061
All right. He's clear, Captain.

113
00:09:08,145 --> 00:09:14,438
Make sure you take a shower, Scofield. You
never know what some women can give you.

114
00:09:16,564 --> 00:09:20,648
♪ Swing low, sweet chariot ♪

115
00:09:21,731 --> 00:09:25,524
♪ Coming for to carry me home ♪

116
00:09:25,816 --> 00:09:27,275
♪ Swing low ♪

117
00:09:27,358 --> 00:09:29,441
You know this one, don't you?

118
00:09:29,525 --> 00:09:33,109
♪ Sweet chariot ♪

119
00:09:33,192 --> 00:09:35,860
♪ Coming for to carry me home ♪

120
00:09:35,943 --> 00:09:40,194
Come on, gimme something.
I thought you was a musical people.

121
00:09:40,278 --> 00:09:43,570
You know, your parents
must be so proud of you, man.

122
00:09:43,653 --> 00:09:45,903
Hitting the trailer park trifecta.

123
00:09:45,987 --> 00:09:50,405
You're a racist, a paedophile, and stupid.

124
00:09:51,363 --> 00:09:56,823
You know, it vexes me that I'm made out
to be the bad guy in the room.

125
00:09:56,906 --> 00:09:59,782
Y'all ain't here
for stealing Girl Scout cookies.

126
00:09:59,866 --> 00:10:03,950
None of us murdered
any Girl Scouts in the process.

127
00:10:04,033 --> 00:10:06,242
Michael's coming back from the boneyard.

128
00:10:06,325 --> 00:10:08,909
Alone, alone.

129
00:10:14,660 --> 00:10:17,661
I tell you all about me,
you don't tell me you're married?

130
00:10:17,744 --> 00:10:19,370
Later.

131
00:10:21,495 --> 00:10:23,538
<i>Rough day, huh, Scofield?</i>

132
00:10:23,621 --> 00:10:27,163
While the rest of us
are in here slinging concrete,

133
00:10:27,247 --> 00:10:31,956
you got some little girl in
to play on your rusty trombone, huh?

134
00:10:32,039 --> 00:10:35,582
Man's got a point.
Itjust doesn't seem equitable, like.

135
00:10:35,665 --> 00:10:41,166
<i>- Shut up and dig, T-Bag.
- What the idiots want to know is,</i>

136
00:10:41,250 --> 00:10:44,710
while we're digging this hole,
what are you doing?

137
00:10:49,544 --> 00:10:52,295
I'm going shopping.

138
00:10:53,378 --> 00:10:55,461
<i>We're good.</i>

139
00:10:56,587 --> 00:10:58,671
All clear.

140
00:11:00,963 --> 00:11:05,089
Credit card? The bulls catch you with that,
they'll be so far up your doggy door...

141
00:11:05,172 --> 00:11:09,007
Don't worry.
They won't be catching me with one.

142
00:11:09,090 --> 00:11:11,674
- How you so sure?
- Because...

143
00:11:12,966 --> 00:11:14,633
I don't have a credit card.

144
00:12:59,241 --> 00:13:00,700
<i>- Nick?</i>

145
00:13:00,783 --> 00:13:03,700
<i>Help! Please...</i>

146
00:13:03,783 --> 00:13:08,826
<i>- Please, I had an accident, my car is totalled.</i>

147
00:13:08,909 --> 00:13:11,910
Is there anybody there?

148
00:13:11,994 --> 00:13:14,911
- We can'tjust ignore him.
- The hell we can't.

149
00:13:14,995 --> 00:13:17,537
<i>Help me. Please!</i>

150
00:13:18,579 --> 00:13:21,204
Help me, please.

151
00:13:21,288 --> 00:13:22,496
Ow! God!

152
00:13:29,373 --> 00:13:31,957
<i>- What happened?
- I must've dozed off.</i>

153
00:13:32,040 --> 00:13:34,291
I've been driving for 12 hours.

154
00:13:34,374 --> 00:13:37,958
- Should I get some water from the well?
- No, the well's dried up.

155
00:13:38,041 --> 00:13:41,834
I think there's a medical kit over here.

156
00:13:46,918 --> 00:13:48,502
No one's going anywhere.

157
00:14:10,591 --> 00:14:13,842
<i>- All right. Say goodbye to Junior.</i>

158
00:14:25,386 --> 00:14:30,304
You know how many pints of blood
the human body has?

159
00:14:30,387 --> 00:14:33,929
The answer is ten. Ten pints.

160
00:14:34,972 --> 00:14:38,514
How many you think Prince Charming
over there on the floor has left?

161
00:14:38,598 --> 00:14:41,015
Eight, going on seven?

162
00:14:42,515 --> 00:14:45,641
I'm gonna take him out to the woodshed,
have a little talk.

163
00:14:45,724 --> 00:14:49,434
In the meantime,
I want you to chew on this.

164
00:14:49,517 --> 00:14:55,059
You tell me everything about the Burrows
case, and who else you've told about it,

165
00:14:55,143 --> 00:15:01,686
and there's a chance that I might let you go
in time to get Mr Savrinn to a doctor.

166
00:15:02,437 --> 00:15:06,812
You decide whose life is more valuable.

167
00:15:06,896 --> 00:15:12,689
The guy waiting to die on death row, or the
guy wishing he'd die out in the woodshed.

168
00:15:25,317 --> 00:15:28,359
<i>One suit, black.</i>

169
00:15:31,444 --> 00:15:32,985
<i>One pair of socks, black.</i>

170
00:15:33,861 --> 00:15:37,111
<i>One pair of shoes. Shoelaces.</i>

171
00:15:39,445 --> 00:15:42,571
<i>One small tape recorder.</i>

172
00:15:46,989 --> 00:15:50,031
<i>One gold watch.</i>

173
00:16:09,744 --> 00:16:12,037
You ever stayed at a fancy hotel, LJ?

174
00:16:12,120 --> 00:16:14,746
You leave your room in the morning,
it's a mess.

175
00:16:14,828 --> 00:16:19,955
Wet dirty towels on the bathroom floor, last
night's room service stinking to high heaven.

176
00:16:20,038 --> 00:16:25,247
Then, you come back at night, it's all gone.

177
00:16:25,331 --> 00:16:27,832
Fresh towels, sheets,
candy on the pillow.

178
00:16:27,915 --> 00:16:31,041
It's just the best feeling in the whole world.

179
00:16:31,124 --> 00:16:36,542
Cos someone else cleaned up your mess.
All you had to do was walk away.

180
00:16:38,709 --> 00:16:41,668
- Don't you hurt them.
- OK.

181
00:16:41,752 --> 00:16:45,419
But you gotta tell me exactly what they know
and who else they've told,

182
00:16:45,502 --> 00:16:48,003
and nobody has to die tonight.

183
00:16:48,086 --> 00:16:53,087
You just walk away.
Let me clean up your mess.

184
00:16:53,171 --> 00:16:57,505
I don't know what's going on.
I swear to God.

185
00:16:57,589 --> 00:17:00,797
Well, I wish I could believe that.

186
00:17:07,424 --> 00:17:10,675
- Bellick assigned me a new cellmate.
- Who'd you get?

187
00:17:10,759 --> 00:17:15,635
Some new fish.
Ran a bump and swipe on an off-duty cop.

188
00:17:15,718 --> 00:17:17,718
Fast hands, faster mouth.

189
00:17:17,801 --> 00:17:20,802
- Yo, what's cracking, my peoples?
- Speak of the devil.

190
00:17:20,886 --> 00:17:24,386
- Michael Scofield, David Apolskis.
- S'up?

191
00:17:24,470 --> 00:17:28,096
I seen you before, right?
You're part of that PI crew.

192
00:17:28,179 --> 00:17:33,264
Maybe you can hook me up. Brother needs to
make some green, some cashish, you know?

193
00:17:33,347 --> 00:17:38,223
- The pay is 19 cents an hour.
- 19 cents? That's slavery, yo.

194
00:17:38,307 --> 00:17:43,350
That's prison, yo.
And besides, PI's all full up for now.

195
00:17:44,516 --> 00:17:46,975
All right. I feel you.

196
00:17:47,059 --> 00:17:50,226
But keep a brother in mind,
if something opens up, yo.

197
00:17:50,310 --> 00:17:55,394
Hell, I'll pay 19 cents an hour
to get me some more time out of the block.

198
00:17:55,478 --> 00:18:00,853
Like having another kid.
Already raised one. I'm too old to do it again.

199
00:18:00,936 --> 00:18:03,854
You ever hear of anything
being stolen from R&D?

200
00:18:03,937 --> 00:18:07,438
Of course.
Bulls steal from personals all the time.

201
00:18:07,521 --> 00:18:11,606
Problem is, you never know what's gone
until you're outside of the walls.

202
00:18:11,689 --> 00:18:16,316
- At that point, you can't do anything about it.
- What if you knew now?

203
00:18:16,399 --> 00:18:20,900
Look, I told you. Leave me out
of whatever it is you've got going.

204
00:18:20,983 --> 00:18:24,525
I just need to know
if you've seen a guard with a gold watch.

205
00:18:24,609 --> 00:18:27,902
There's a lot of people
can get you a gold watch in here.

206
00:18:27,985 --> 00:18:31,986
<i>- Yeah, but I need this specific gold watch.
- Westmoreland.</i>

207
00:18:32,070 --> 00:18:35,653
Pope wants to see you. Let's go.

208
00:18:37,154 --> 00:18:39,821
Look, I haven't seen nothing.

209
00:18:39,905 --> 00:18:45,281
But there is this one CO.
Word is he's the worst thief in here.

210
00:18:48,698 --> 00:18:51,324
My wife faxed this over
from County Records.

211
00:18:51,407 --> 00:18:55,408
Copy of Scofield's marriage licence.
She says you owe her, big time.

212
00:18:55,492 --> 00:18:58,950
Looks legit. He wasn't trying
to sneak in some whore for a conjugal.

213
00:18:59,034 --> 00:19:02,618
Says here they got married
the day before Scofield robbed that bank.

214
00:19:02,701 --> 00:19:05,911
Why the hell would he do that?

215
00:19:12,454 --> 00:19:15,205
- Heard from Veronica?
- No.

216
00:19:16,954 --> 00:19:20,331
<i>Just a note from LJ
saying he was with her, he's safe.</i>

217
00:19:20,414 --> 00:19:25,957
But it's been a while.
Doesn't feel right. Feels wrong.

218
00:19:26,999 --> 00:19:29,458
- I gotta go.
- Really wrong.

219
00:19:29,541 --> 00:19:31,083
<i>I'll see you.</i>

220
00:19:38,251 --> 00:19:42,252
<i>I, uh... I've come to a realisation.</i>

221
00:19:42,336 --> 00:19:45,504
Either Ms Donovan and that boy
don't like you very much,

222
00:19:45,587 --> 00:19:50,546
or they have an unreasonable amount of faith
in your cardiovascular system.

223
00:19:50,630 --> 00:19:52,880
So tell me, Nick.

224
00:19:52,963 --> 00:19:57,672
This all you got? This paper trail
of an indictment that never even happened?

225
00:19:57,756 --> 00:19:59,173
Is this it?

226
00:19:59,256 --> 00:20:03,758
We know you don't have a surveillance tape
any more, you have nobody to testify.

227
00:20:03,841 --> 00:20:06,758
So is this really all you've got?

228
00:20:08,342 --> 00:20:12,802
Mr Savrinn, that bullet
went through your teres major,

229
00:20:12,885 --> 00:20:17,886
ripped the lateral margin of your scapula,
leaving you no medial rotation of your arm.

230
00:20:17,969 --> 00:20:21,178
So if you try to swing
that piece of lumber at me...

231
00:20:21,261 --> 00:20:22,845
Argh!

232
00:20:22,929 --> 00:20:27,930
It's gonna feel like
your arm is ripping out of its socket.

233
00:20:29,013 --> 00:20:32,306
Come on, Nick. Mr Project Justice.

234
00:20:32,389 --> 00:20:35,265
We both know why
you're really here, don't we?

235
00:20:35,349 --> 00:20:39,058
And it ain't to save Lincoln Burrows' life.

236
00:20:42,683 --> 00:20:45,267
<i>All prisoners, 15 minutes of walk time.</i>

237
00:20:45,351 --> 00:20:49,727
 Inside these walls, I creep and
I crawl, looking for a way out ?

238
00:20:49,809 --> 00:20:52,144
♪ But I know there's
gonna be no easy route ♪

239
00:20:52,228 --> 00:20:55,686
